OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMet chief apologises to    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FLGBT+ activist over past   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ffailings                   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Metropolitan Police Commissioner,  
OL,6, Sir Mark Rowley, has apologised to     
OL,7, LGBT+ campaigner Peter Tatchell for the
OL,8, force's homophobic failings.           
OL,10,FIn what Mr Tatchell said was a         
OL,11,F"ground-breaking step forward", Sir    
OL,12,FMark's letter said he was "sorry to all
OL,13,Fof the communities we have let down".  
OL,15,FA damning report by Baroness Casey in  
OL,16,FMarch found there was racism, misogyny 
OL,17,Fand homophobia in the Met Police.      
OL,19,FMr Tatchell said the apology "draws a  
OL,20,Fline under past Met persecution".      
